{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4560daeb-8c4a-4c0f-a655-b42a4adfc567","content":"I can help point you in the right direction! Analyzing a `.dmp` file is a post-mortem debugging task. Here are the main tools you can use:\n\n### `dotnet-dump analyze`\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <your-file.dmp>\n```\nThen inside the interactive session:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap overview\n- `threads` — list all threads\n\n### LLDB (Linux)\n```bash\nlldb --core <your-file.dmp>\nplugin load libsosplugin.so\nclrstack\n```\n\n### Visual Studio (Windows)\nOpen the `.dmp` file directly — it provides a rich UI for inspecting threads, exceptions, and memory.\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` and start an interactive analysis session on a specific file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b45f4279-68ad-48b1-9dc9-dac53b889dbd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\" So I should NOT invoke that skill.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing crash dumps.","outputTokens":329,"requestId":"1B96:286828:E07AF3:100B433:6A02882C"},"id":"97afade6-f3d3-40c1-831b-266a9fd0898d","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:53:58.851Z","parentId":"d9bd1607-b902-43c1-ac45-4daa186c2b20"}
